---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../../components/Hero.astro';
import { url } from '../../lib/site';
---
<BaseLayout title="Reviewing Guidelines">
  <Hero
    eyebrow="Resources · Reviewing Guidelines"
    title="Reviewing Guidelines"
    lead="How to write fair, constructive, and useful reviews for ML4H."
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>The reviewer's role</h2>
      <p>
        ML4H reviews are the backbone of the community. As a reviewer, your job
        is to help the program chairs make good decisions and to give authors
        actionable feedback — regardless of the outcome.
      </p>

      <h3>What to evaluate</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Relevance.</strong> Is the work within scope for ML4H?</li>
        <li><strong>Novelty.</strong> What is new relative to prior work?</li>
        <li><strong>Technical soundness.</strong> Are the methods correct and well-described?</li>
        <li><strong>Experimental rigor.</strong> Are baselines appropriate? Are results reproducible?</li>
        <li><strong>Clinical validity.</strong> Does the clinical context justify the approach?</li>
        <li><strong>Clarity.</strong> Is the paper well-written and easy to follow?</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Tone and constructiveness</h3>
      <p>
        Reviews should be respectful and professional. Critique the work, not the
        authors. Be specific: if something is unclear or incorrect, say exactly
        what and why. Offer suggestions for improvement where possible.
      </p>

      <h3>Conflicts of interest</h3>
      <p>
        Declare any conflicts of interest to the area chairs immediately.
        Do not review work from authors at your institution, former advisees
        or advisors, or anyone with whom you have a close personal relationship.
      </p>

      <div class="btn-row">
        <a class="btn btn-outline" href={url('resources/review-policy')}>Review Policy</a>
        <a class="btn btn-outline" href={url('resources')}>Back to Resources</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
